net.sf.jclec.mo.strategy

Class MOPSOStrategy

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.strategy.MOStrategy
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.strategy.MOPSOStrategy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OMOPSO

    public abstract class MOPSOStrategy
extends MOStrategy
    Abstract strategy for a multi-objective PSO (MOPSO) algorithm. It specifies the required structure of the methods that any MOPSO algorithm should implement, in addition to those specified by MOStrategy: the turbulence mechanism, the update of positions and the update of velocities. The execution control of the search process is performed by a MOPSOAlgorithm, so it will invoke the specific methods of the strategy. The algorithm is also in charge of updating the execution context that might be required to perform some operations in the strategy.

    History:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.
